.TH SINGINE-EDGE 1 "2026-03-17" "singine 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
singine-edge \- build, deploy, and manage the Collibra edge server stack
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B singine edge
.I FAMILY
[\fICOMMAND\fR]
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B singine edge
is the lifecycle management surface for the Collibra edge server stack at
.IR ~/ws/git/github/sindoc/collibra/edge/ .
It orchestrates three container images, a docker compose stack, and a Claude
API artifact-generation agent through a single command hierarchy.
.PP
The stack is built on a
.B CentOS 7 LTS
base image and provides:
.TP
.B CentOS 7 LTS base image
.RI ( sindoc-collibra-edge-base )
Java 11, EPEL tooling, and a non-root
.I edge
user.  All other images derive FROM this base.
.TP
.B Collibra DGC Edge node
.RI ( sindoc-collibra-edge )
Runs the Collibra Data Governance Center Edge JAR.  Registers with the
central Collibra DGC instance and activates configured capabilities
(CONNECT, CATALOG, LINEAGE, PROFILING, SITE, WORKFLOW).
.TP
.B Edge Site server
.RI ( sindoc-collibra-edge-site )
A lightweight Java HTTP server implementing the Collibra Edge Site REST API
contract
.RI ( /api/edge/v1/\fI*\fR ).
Hosts static and dynamic web content under
.IR /site/ .
Registers itself with Collibra DGC using a site registration key.
.TP
.B CDN proxy
.RI ( sindoc-collibra-cdn )
nginx TLS-terminating reverse proxy.  Routes external HTTPS traffic to the
edge site server and the DGC edge node.  Caches CDN-eligible responses.
.PP
The stack root is
.I ~/ws/git/github/sindoc/collibra/edge/
by default.
Override with the environment variable
.BR COLLIBRA_EDGE_DIR .
.SH COMMAND FAMILIES
.TP
.B build
Build one or all container images.  Delegates to the stack
.BR Makefile .
.TP
.B push
Tag and push images to a container registry.
.TP
.B up / down
Start or stop the compose stack.
.TP
.B logs
Tail container log output.
.TP
.B status
Show images, running containers, and governance decision URN in one view.
.TP
.B install
Full install: build all images, prepare the agent Python virtualenv, and
register a governance decision.  Idempotent.
.TP
.B deploy
.B install
followed by
.BR "up --detach" .
Brings the full stack to a running state from scratch.
.TP
.B agent
Manage the Claude API edge-agent that generates Kubernetes, OpenShift, and
Collibra configuration artifacts for RHEL 7.7\(en7.9 hosts.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.SS build
.TP
.B singine edge build [\fB--target\fR \fITARGET\fR] [\fB--tag\fR \fITAG\fR] [\fB--no-cache\fR] [\fB--json\fR]
Build container image(s).
.RS
.TP
.B --target \fITARGET\fR
Which image to build.
.I TARGET
is one of
.IR base ,
.IR collibra-edge ,
.IR cdn ,
.I all
(default:
.IR all ).
.TP
.B --tag \fITAG\fR
Docker image tag.  Default:
.IR local .
.TP
.B --no-cache
Pass
.B --no-cache
to the Docker build.
.TP
.B --json
Emit a JSON envelope with build outcome and metadata.
.RE
.SS push
.TP
.B singine edge push \fB--registry\fR \fIREGISTRY\fR [\fB--target\fR \fITARGET\fR] [\fB--tag\fR \fITAG\fR] [\fB--json\fR]
Tag local images and push to a container registry.
.RS
.TP
.B --registry \fIREGISTRY\fR
Registry hostname, e.g.
.IR registry.example.com .
Required.
.TP
.B --target \fITARGET\fR
Which image(s) to push.  Same values as
.B build
(default:
.IR all ).
.TP
.B --tag \fITAG\fR
Tag to push (default:
.IR local ).
.RE
.SS up
.TP
.B singine edge up [\fB--detach\fR] [\fB--json\fR]
Start the edge stack via
.BR docker\ compose\ up .
With
.B --detach
.RI ( -d ),
runs containers in the background.
.SS down
.TP
.B singine edge down [\fB--json\fR]
Stop and remove all stack containers via
.BR docker\ compose\ down .
.SS logs
.TP
.B singine edge logs [\fB--service\fR \fISERVICE\fR] [\fB--follow\fR]
Print or tail container logs.
.B --service
restricts output to
.I collibra-edge
or
.IR cdn .
.B --follow
.RI ( -f )
streams live output.
.SS status
.TP
.B singine edge status [\fB--json\fR]
Show a combined view of:
.IP \(bu 2
Local Docker images matching
.IR sindoc-collibra* :
name, tag, size, age.
.IP \(bu 2
Running compose services: name, state, health.
.IP \(bu 2
Governance decision URN from
.IR ~/.singine/decisions/edge-agent.json .
.SS install
.TP
.B singine edge install [\fB--tag\fR \fITAG\fR] [\fB--json\fR]
Full install in three steps:
.IP 1. 4
.B build
\(em build all images with the given tag.
.IP 2. 4
.B agent prepare
\(em create the Python virtualenv and install dependencies.
.IP 3. 4
.B agent install
\(em register a governance decision via
.B singine decide edge-agent
(with offline fallback).
.PP
Idempotent.  Re-running after a partial failure resumes from the failed step.
.SS deploy
.TP
.B singine edge deploy [\fB--tag\fR \fITAG\fR] [\fB--json\fR]
Equivalent to
.B install
followed by
.BR "up --detach" .
The canonical one-command bring-up for a fresh environment.
.SS agent
.TP
.B singine edge agent \fICOMMAND\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
Manage the Claude API edge-agent under
.IR edge/agent/ .
.RS
.TP
.B validate [\fB--json\fR]
Smoke-test all six agent tools without making an Anthropic API call.
Confirms
.I tools.py
and
.I edge_agent.py
are structurally healthy.
.TP
.B run \fB--task\fR \fITASK\fR [\fB--output-dir\fR \fIDIR\fR] [\fB--json\fR]
Run the agent with a natural-language task.  Requires
.B ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
to be set.  Generated artifacts are written to
.I edge/agent/output/
by default.  Override with
.BR --output-dir .
.TP
.B install [\fB--json\fR]
Prepare agent virtualenv and register governance decision.
Equivalent to
.BR "make -C edge/agent install" .
.TP
.B status [\fB--json\fR]
Print virtualenv path, Python version, anthropic package version, artifact
count, and governance decision URN.
.RE
.SH EDGE SITE
The edge site server
.RI ( sindoc-collibra-edge-site )
implements the Collibra Edge Site REST API and serves web content.
.PP
.B REST API surface
.PP
.nf
GET  /health
GET  /api/edge/v1/status
POST /api/edge/v1/register
GET  /api/edge/v1/capabilities
POST /api/edge/v1/capabilities/{type}/invoke
.fi
.PP
.B Supported capability types
.PP
.TP
.B connect
JDBC data source connectivity for on-premises data sampling.
.TP
.B catalog
Asset metadata push to the central Collibra catalog.
.TP
.B lineage
Technical lineage collection from on-premises pipelines.
.TP
.B profiling
On-premises data profiling and classification.
.TP
.B site
Static and dynamic web content served under
.IR /site/ .
Does not require a DGC connection.
.TP
.B workflow
On-premises workflow step execution triggered by Collibra DGC.
.PP
The Java interface contract for the edge site is in
.I edge/java/src/main/java/io/sindoc/collibra/edge/
and is built with:
.PP
.nf
./gradlew javadoc jar
.fi
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B COLLIBRA_EDGE_DIR
Override the default stack root
.RI ( ~/ws/git/github/sindoc/collibra/edge/ ).
.TP
.B COLLIBRA_EDGE_HOSTNAME
FQDN of the edge node.  Required by
.B docker compose
and by the edge site server.
.TP
.B COLLIBRA_DGC_URL
Base URL of the central Collibra DGC instance.  Required for DGC registration.
.TP
.B COLLIBRA_EDGE_SITE_ID
Stable identifier for the edge site registration.
.TP
.B COLLIBRA_EDGE_REG_KEY
Registration key issued by Collibra DGC.  Kept in
.I .env
(gitignored).
.TP
.B ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
Required by
.B singine edge agent run .
.TP
.B SINGINE_SESSION_TOKEN
Included in
.B singine runtime exec-external
payloads for audit tracing.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/ws/git/github/sindoc/collibra/edge/
Stack root.  All paths below are relative to this directory.
.TP
.I Makefile
Top-level build/deploy/clean targets.
.TP
.I docker-compose.yml
Defines the
.IR cdn ,
.IR collibra-edge ,
and
.I edge-site
services.
.TP
.I .env.example
Copy to
.I .env
and populate before running the stack.
.TP
.I image/base/Dockerfile
CentOS 7 LTS base: Java 11, EPEL, non-root
.I edge
user.
.TP
.I image/collibra-edge/Dockerfile
Collibra DGC Edge node.  Requires
.I collibra-edge.jar
from the Collibra Customer Portal.
.TP
.I image/edge-site/Dockerfile
Collibra-compatible edge site server.  Hosts the Edge Site REST API and
optional web content.
.TP
.I image/cdn/Dockerfile
nginx CDN proxy with TLS termination.
.TP
.I java/
Java interface layer
.RI ( io.sindoc.collibra.edge ).
Build with
.BR "./gradlew javadoc jar" .
.TP
.I agent/
Claude API edge-agent.  See
.BR singine-edge-agent (1).
.TP
.I ~/.singine/decisions/edge-agent.json
Governance decision record (offline fallback).
.SH PREREQUISITES
.TP
.B Before running \(fqsingine edge build\(fq
Docker must be installed and the Docker daemon must be running.
.TP
.B Before running \(fqsingine edge up\(fq or \(fqsingine edge deploy\(fq
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.I image/collibra-edge/collibra-edge.jar
\(em download from the Collibra Customer Portal
.RI ( productresources.collibra.com ).
.IP \(bu 2
.I certs/server.crt
and
.I certs/server.key
\(em TLS certificate and key for the CDN.
.IP \(bu 2
.I .env
\(em copy from
.I .env.example
and set
.B COLLIBRA_EDGE_HOSTNAME
and
.BR COLLIBRA_DGC_URL .
.RE
.TP
.B Before running \(fqsingine edge agent run\(fq
.B ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
must be set to a valid Anthropic API key.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
# One-command bring-up from a clean environment.
singine edge deploy

# Build only the CDN image with a release tag.
singine edge build --target cdn --tag v1.2.0

# Push all images to a private registry.
singine edge push --registry registry.example.com --tag v1.2.0

# Check what is running and the governance decision.
singine edge status --json

# Tail CDN logs.
singine edge logs --service cdn --follow

# Validate agent tools without an API call.
singine edge agent validate

# Generate a Kubernetes Deployment for Collibra edge on RHEL 7.9.
export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
singine edge agent run \\
  --task "Generate a Collibra edge Deployment and firewalld zone for RHEL 7.9" \\
  --output-dir /tmp/edge-out
.fi
